\title{Check Whether Your Prior Settings Are Reasonable Before Fitting}
\description{
Before running a potentially long MCMC analysis with
\code{\link{fitRateScape}}, it is good practice to verify that your prior
settings produce biologically sensible behavior. This function does that
by simulating many datasets under your specified priors and showing you
what kinds of data they produce.

\strong{Why bother?} If your prior on rate variation is too diffuse, the
model may explore unrealistic scenarios (e.g., some branches evolving
1000x faster than others). If it is too tight, you may miss real rate
shifts. This function helps you find the sweet spot.

The function produces diagnostic plots and warnings if potential problems
are detected. Run this once before committing to a long fitting run —
it is much faster than the full MCMC and can save you from wasting time
with bad prior settings.
